gloss.term:
Usually a reference to five hindrances: longing
                                for sense pleasures (Skt. kāmacchanda), malice (Skt. vyāpāda), sloth and torpor (Skt. styānamiddha),
                                excitement and remorse (Skt. auddhatyakaukṛtya), and doubt (Skt. vicikitsā).
